description:
IngredientDto.unit is a free-form String today. Every downstream consumer ends up doing string-matching to recover the structure that should have been typed in the first place: unit_converter.rs normalizes 'lb/lbs/pound/pounds' via lowercasing + aliasing; ShoppingService aggregation's 'unit equality' drifts on whitespace/case; the staples classifier in fewd-wm6 keys on string matches; the rounding classifier in fewd-p3j will too; every new consumer inherits the same tax.

Target shape: strict enum, no escape hatch.

    pub enum Unit {
        // Weight
        Gram, Kilogram, Ounce, Pound,
        // Volume
        Milliliter, Liter, Teaspoon, Tablespoon, Cup, Quart, Gallon, FluidOunce,
        // Count / discrete
        Each, Whole, Head, Clove, Bunch, Piece,
        // Qualitative
        Pinch, Dash, Splash, ToTaste, AsNeeded, ForGarnish,
    }

serde Serialize/Deserialize with snake_case; FromStr handles existing aliasing (lb/lbs/pound → Pound); Display returns the canonical short form. Helpers: is_qualitative(), category() returning Weight/Volume/Count/Qualitative, convert_to(target, value).

Unknown units at ingest REJECT rather than fall back — return a clear error listing valid units. The enum is the source of truth; if a legitimate unit is missing, expand the enum deliberately rather than silently accommodate drift. Drift-proof by construction.

Migration: existing stored rows with unrecognized unit strings get normalized as part of rolling this out (see fewd-data-migration-posture memory). Write a one-shot migration that attempts FromStr on each ingredient's unit; logs any that fail so the maintainer can inspect + expand the enum before running again.

Scope: enum + impls in server/src/dto/unit.rs, migrate IngredientDto.unit from String to Unit, walk every callsite (unit_converter.rs, ShoppingService aggregator, cooking-mode display, recipe edit form, MCP IngredientOut), plus the one-shot normalization migration.

Orthogonal to the shopping-list work in flight (fewd-p3j/wm6/kif/xez). They can use string-unit logic today and swap to the enum when this lands. The staples and rounding classifiers benefit directly — they stop string-matching and start category-matching.
